THE KIBITZER
By JOHN on
Do you play bridge just to get good hands? If you do the odds
are started against you. Take for example the following hypothetical situation: you are dealer and you deal yourself a hand without
looking at it. What are the. odds for getting a good hand?
One hand in four will be good enough for an opening bid (this.
teen or more high card points). Of the other three, two hands wrli
fall between seven and twelve points, and the remaining hand in
four will have six or less points.
of your opening hands, only three iii eight will have fifteen or
